        <updateDate>2021-03-22T18:20:25Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Recognition of Local Interests in NEPA Decision Making</b></p> <p>This bill sets forth requirements for determining the venue for judicial review of an agency action under the National Environmental Policy Act of 1969 (NEPA). Specifically, the bill requires a proceeding for judicial review of an agency's compliance with NEPA to be brought in the U.S. district court for a district in which the authorized activity is proposed to be carried out or the U.S. District Court for the District of Columbia.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
